GNU External Ballistics Library (libballistics)
v1.1

What is libballistics?
----------------------

A C library for numerically solving exerior ballistics problems. The library 
supports standard drag models (G1-G8) and calculations for most common forms 
of output. The solution method employs the common "3 degrees of freedom" 
analysis found in many commercial tools.

Using libballistics
-------------------

To build libballistics, invoke the following commands:

./configure
make
make install

See the file src/example.c for a working example of how to use the library.
